---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About | Offsite Social Co." description="The story behind the club." />
		<style>
			/* We use the exact same styles here to keep the brand consistent */
			:root {
				--bg-color: #0f2e26;
				--text-main: #f5e6d3;
				--accent: #e08b6c;
				--card-bg: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
			}
			body {
				background-color: var(--bg-color);
				color: var(--text-main);
				font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}
			.container {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 4rem 2rem;
			}
			.header-nav {
				margin-bottom: 4rem;
			}
			.header-nav a {
				color: var(--text-main);
				text-decoration: none;
				font-family: sans-serif;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				font-size: 0.8rem;
				letter-spacing: 1px;
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
				padding-bottom: 2px;
			}
			h1 {
				font-size: 3rem;
				font-weight: normal;
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(245, 230, 211, 0.3);
				padding-bottom: 1rem;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}
			p {
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main class="container">
			<nav class="header-nav">
				<a href="/">← Back to the Block</a>
			</nav>

			<h1>About the Project</h1>
			
			<p>Offsite Social Co. was built on a simple observation: the shift to remote work gave us our time back, but it stripped away the passive routines that actually tie a neighborhood together.</p>
			
			<p>Working from home shouldn't mean working in isolation. We don't need more digital groups or forced networking events with name tags. We need a reason to clock out, grab a seat at a familiar table, and be a regular.</p>
			
			<p>This club acts as a bridge. By partnering with distinct local spots that care about their craft, we create unhurried windows of time for neighbors to cross paths.</p>

			<p>Operated by Community Craft, Ltd., this is an independent effort to build something durable. Block by block.</p>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>